						<div class="postbody">In reply to <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=67322#67322" class="postlink">this post</a>:
<br />
<br />For what it's worth, GPL doesn't "infect" across the boundary between one executable and another. (See the <a href="http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-faq.html#MereAggregation" class="postlink">discussion of "aggregate"</a>.) I'd guess that two programs in one disc image or ROM image are separate executables if they have a relationship similar to the menu program and games on a multicart: 1. they are cleanly concatenated from separately linked binaries, and 2. any communication between them is over a documented protocol with the same nature as pipes or command-line arguments.</div>

					
