					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The way I figure it, the ROM is just a copy of memory, in the same way a PC is required to load (for example) both windows and a GPL program into memory at the same time, to run it.  The NES has no need for any loading, and the program to use the 'multicart' or whatnot, is essentially a custom operating system (even if it is really simple).  There is just no other way it can work.
<br />
<br />I suppose looking into how GPL applies to software on embedded (too small for linux) devices would be more appropriate than making a PC comparison, though.  About that, I have no idea.</div>

